zenity --title="Welcome" --warning --text="This is a third party fan made distribution!

===========================================
Built: $(cat /etc/builddate)
===========================================

Click on the I icon in the panel for information 
about key bindings, and Programs"


zenity --title="Help" --info --text 'Weston Key Bindings:
=================================================================================
Note: The super key on most keyboards is the Windows logo key.
Note: The middle mouse button is usually pressing the scroll button on most mice.
=================================================================================

Zoom the display in and out: Super key + scroll wheel

Terminate Active Application: Super key + K
Move Window: Super key + left mouse button                    
Resize Window: Super key + middle mouse button
Switch Windows: Super key + tab                              
Change Window opacity: Super key + alt key + scroll wheel
Rotate Window: Super key: right mouse button

Save a screenshot: Super key + s
Start and stop video recording: Super key + r 
(after recording run weston-video-convert in the panel to convert the capture file to a .webm video file)

Dim the display (under native Weston): Super key + F9
Brighten the display (under native Weston): Super key + F10


Switch workspaces: Super key + up arrow/down arrow (or Super key + workspace Function # key)
By default there are 2 workspaces

Exit Weston: ctrl key + alt key + backspace' 

zenity --title="Help" --info --text '
=================================================================================
=================================================================================
The Application menu stays open, even after calling programs, and does not work with multiple instances of the Application Launcher 

To launch another Application, currently, you have to find the already open instance of the Application Launcher

Some applications (mostly xwayland applications) might need to be resized to refresh the contents of the window.'


zenity --title="Help" --info --text 'To launch programs:
=================================================================================
=================================================================================
Click on the "RBOS" Icon on the top for the Application menu. Be sure to check for the Wayland programs under "Applications"!

Click on the Desktop icon for viewing the contents of the Desktop folder

Click on the drive icon for the Removable Media Manager

Click on the Globe icon for the Snowshoe Web Browser

Click on the Terminal icon for a Wayland Terminal with Wayland variables

Click on the Xorg logo for a Xterm with X variables

Click the Speaker icon to adjust the volume

Click on the Antenna icon to launch the Network Manager

The movie icon converts the Weston screenshot file to .WEBM files as mentioned in the previous dialog

Click on the lightbulb icon for battery info

The I icon launches these help dialogs 

Click on the red X icon for shutdown options
'


